    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Animation technique that implements a courvoisier set-up, or grouping, in which figures are trimmed to their edges, glued to a background typically composed of wood veneer, patterns, or hand-painted watercolors, and covered by a protective top cel. The technique was developed by the Courvoisier Galleries in the late 1930s and early 1940s. </Note_Text>
